  "overview": "LLVM's new pass manager (NPM) uses a type-erased, template-based design. A pass is any C++ object with a run(IRUnit&, AnalysisManager&) method. PassManager<IRUnitT> holds a vector of type-erased PassConcept pointers and executes them in insertion order. Analyses are registered separately in AnalysisManager<IRUnitT> and computed lazily on demand. The legacy pass manager (LPM) uses a global PassRegistry singleton populated by INITIALIZE_PASS macros or RegisterPass<T> constructors. The two systems coexist; the NPM is the default for opt and clang.",
